<p>A few months back, me and Roget were discussing ideas by which we could increase the visibility of tales. We discussed this and we both concluded that we'd really like to see a tale project with <em>scale</em>: something large and frightening in scope that rocks canon to its core, that tears your envisioning of the Foundation from tip to toe as you realise just what you've read.</p>
<p>Whether it's Incident 239-B's large-scale havoc involving giants of the site canon throwing down against one another with an innocent girl's life in the balance, Duke 'til Dawn's pinnacle of self-insert insanity or the slow, creeping, painful dissection of a major character's psyche in In His Own Image, when they're done right tales can split the readerbase in twain and shape the future of site canons for years to come.</p>
<p>Is it too early to say whether or not this is one of them?</p>
<p>Probably, but it won't stop me applauding you on writing one of the most ambitious, well-written and deeply immersive pieces of fiction on this site.</p>
<p>I hope to see someone cite this as a reason why they came to the site in the same way hundreds of newbies have been pulled in by the decommissionings, the Duchamps and the Game Days. Well done.</p>

							</div>

								
					
