																		Whooo.
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/adminbright" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(224440); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=224440&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183123" alt="AdminBright" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=224440)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/adminbright" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(224440); return false;" >AdminBright</a></span> <span class="odate time_1496979951 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">09 Jun 2017 03:45</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2847320">
									

<p>Well. This is&#8230; this is something else really.</p>
<p>This is quite frankly amazing. There are hints, and references to Bright canon in here that just make my day and squee&#8230; Stuff like gambling, or him making moonshine.</p>
<p>And you're right, it's not canon. The Bright family were city dwellers. There's no mention of Sarah. Their family, or their father at least, wouldn't have left them alone like that.</p>
<p>But, that being said, I'm not critting it for canon. This is&#8230; freaking amazing. I mean, uneblievably huge, and awesome, and&#8230; There are things here that fit in despite me not ever putting them out, mostly in the relationships between peoples.</p>
<p>(Also, I've been trying to write an SCP about Space Oddity for YEARS.)</p>
<p>Honestly&#8230; yes, it's not-canon. But, in my head, it's not-canon in the same way as Unfinished Business. It's not what I would have done with the characters. It's not nessacarily using all of my head canon. But whereas some stories are simply Not. Canon. This is OFFICIALLY Not-Canon. Like, I'm proud to have created the characters that were used in this.</p>
<p>I really like how bits feel pulled from my brain, like how the first bit doesn't use any names, something I often avoid in my writings. I like how you took it and made it your own, even after hearing from me what I considered canon. Honestly, in my head, it does kind of make me wanna change Bright to depressive before the amulet. It makes sense.</p>
<p>Not only that, but you stumbled on a power I didn't know he had&#8230; The universe refuses to let Bright die. Something always happens&#8230; until it found an easy way to keep him safe.</p>
<p>Hmmm.</p>
<p>Wishing I could vote multiple times, all of them Plus.</p>
<p>(also congrats on getting the longest response from me in&#8230; I think ever.)</p>

							</div>

