																		Bright Family Reference
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/thefriendlyvandal" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2064544); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2064544&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183123" alt="thefriendlyvandal" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2064544)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/thefriendlyvandal" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2064544); return false;" >thefriendlyvandal</a></span> <span class="odate time_1497058967 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">10 Jun 2017 01:42</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2848124">
									

<p>Hey, I'm kinda realizing here that some people have not been also intensely reading Bright family canon for 8 months now, so I'm just gonna kinda insert the family reference chart we built in the SCP Shitposting discord here:</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Show&nbsp;hell&nbsp;map</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Hide&nbsp;hell&nbsp;map</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content"><img src="https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/275799201927921666/276898734258913281/fadosfjdafm.png" alt="fadosfjdafm.png" class="image" /></div>
</div>
</div>
<p>This also isn't a full reference, either. Like, duckman likes to change his canon, which is cool but like. Help</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Show&nbsp;brightcanon.jpg</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Hide&nbsp;brightcanon.jpg</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content"><img src="https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/275799201927921666/277893013546467337/Screen_Shot_2017-01-30_at_1.01.43_PM.png" alt="Screen_Shot_2017-01-30_at_1.01.43_PM.png" class="image" /></div>
</div>
</div>
<p>And yeah, a few minor discrepancies in this tale:<br />
1. As Duckman said, I didn't mention <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-321">Sarah</a>. I actually thought about inserting a chapter with Mikell and Jack reminiscing on their experience of their mom's stillbirth (burying the empty box and stuff, but their parents never mention it again and they aren't aware of their sibling until they enter the Foundation) but I was afraid it would pull from the focus of the piece.</p>
<p>2. Mikell has two children; in Duckman's canon he only has one. Take this as you will.<br />
EDIT: after looking at the map, this is already true. Good for me.</p>
<p>3. Canonically, Claire can see the future, but not change the timeline to suit her needs as she does during Mikell's rodeo in this tale. That being said, she's referenced as a very powerful seer in other tales.</p>
<p>4. Other Bright family reading from Duckman's canon:<br />
-<a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/iquit">&quot;I Quit&quot;</a><br />
-<a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/heretherebe">Here There Be</a> (I ignore this one, mostly because it hasn't happened yet for the majority of the tale, or maybe doesn't happen at all)<br />
-<a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/rip">RIP</a><br />
-<a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/codebrown">Code Brown</a><br />
-<a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/whatislove">What Is Love?</a><br />
-<a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/nothingtoseehere">Nothing to See Here</a> (Linked and referenced in Mikell's sidepage in this tale)<br />
-<a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/blinddate">Blind Date</a><br />
-And then of course, like, 45 other ones that relate in one way or another, but the main canon one regarding family dynamics- and the one I was kind of enchanted/entranced by, and still am- Is Code Brown.</p>
<p>5. One of the things I played a lot with in this tale was the idea that all of the Bright kids were born anomolous in one way or another, like a genetic trait. Mikell's- and this isn't quite obvious, but I'm rolling with it- is his connection to the guns, which are heavily anomalous and in some ways sapient artifacts that don't really accept owners unconditionally, at least in this tale.</p>
<p>6. I was worried about this tale because it doesn't really match with these other Bright tales in a lot of ways, but mostly in tone/subject matter. Duckman's tales are enchanting, wild, lighthearted but complex tales that have quite a bit of humor. They don't take themselves seriously. This one is meant to be dark, rich, emotional, and striking. For a while, I had this named <em>Midwestern Gothic</em>, and I would still put it in the Gothic genre to some degree; it's connected to nature, to environments, to emotions and similar feelings of numbness and anger felt by someone in Jack's position as he learns how to work with his mental health as he enters his adult life, and how his position as a Director/contained artifact affects that. It's unusually serious subject manner.</p>

							</div>

								
